On the shorter side and outside off, Das goes after it but is beaten. A loose stroke to end a good over for Bangladesh.
Tosses it up on middle, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Another flighted ball on middle, Hasan plays it to mid-wicket again.
Fuller, this is pushed to the right of the bowler who stops it.
Well bowled! This is tossed up nicely. Hasan looks to defend but does so inside the line. It goes off the outer half through point for one.
Flatter and on off, Das works it to short leg.
Fired on the stumps, Liton is solid in defense.

Just short! Excellent effort from Cornwall! This is a short one on off, Hasan looks to fend at it but the bounce gets big on him. It hits the splice and lobs towards gully. Cornwall there moves to his right and then dives forward but it lands short.
Another short one on the body this time, ducked under.
Looks to bowl it short again but this is down the leg side. Left alone.
Slashes and misses! Not sure if that is the right shot with deep point and third man in place! Short and wide outside off, Hasan throws his bat at it but misses.
Goes back to ducking now probably because this is on his body.
Good length and on off, Hasan pushes this towards cover for one.
A single as this is eased down to long on.

OUT! There is a spike as the ball passes the bat and West Indies have got the breakthrough they so desperately needed! Liton Das fails to make most of the start he got! Cornwall is the man to get the wicket once again. He has all three to fall today. Das looks to play the paddle sweep. It lands outside off and then turns back in. It seems to have gone off the inner half, then onto the pads and lobs towards the left of the keeper. Blackwood from the first slip moves there and takes it. An appeal and the finger is raised. Das reviews. He then checks his position to see if he is hit outside the line. He though has been given out caught. Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows a spike. Das walks back and takes a review along. End of a superb inning from him but he needed to bat longer. Bangladesh trail by 128. Can Windies take a lead of above 100 now?
On off, defended.

DROPPED! That should have been taken! Cornwall should have got his fifth there! This lands on off and then goes on with the arm. Hasan looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge straight to first slip where Blackwood spills it.

OUT! TAKEN THIS TIME! Cornwall gets his fifth! What a spell of bowling especially today! Take a bow and all of a sudden, the Windies are back in control of this game. Two wickets in the over has changed the complexion of it completely. This is on middle, once again Hasan looks to defend but does so inside the line. It goes off the outside edge to Blackwood who takes it by moving to his right. Hasan actually looked to play that with a closed face of the bat. The drift away from middle did him in.
A single! Islam will be on strike in the next over! On the pads, this is worked through square leg for one.
Banged short and on middle, Taijul clips it towards square leg and changes ends.
Short again. This is around the body. Meidy does well to keep it out.
One more short ball from Shannon. Mehdiy sits under it.

OUT! TAKEN! Another one bites the dust. Gabriel is fired up. Mehidy's defiance is over now. After banging three balls short, Gabriel overpitches it and bowls it wide too. Mehidy sees the scoring opportunity. He goes after it but ends up hitting it uppishly straight to the cover fielder. Skipper Brathwaite makes no mistake. Mehidy cannot believe his luck. A fine, fine knock but Bangladesh have fallen apart here. The umpire wants to check the back foot. Third umpire comes in. One replay is enough to send Mehidy packing.
Wide outside off, Abu lets it.
Brilliant yorker from Gabriel. Jayed does well to block it out. End of another successful over for West Indies.

Tossed up and outside off, Taijul looks to drive but the ball spins away a touch. It takes the outside edge and races to third man. A fielder from the ring chases it and stops nears the fence. Two taken.
Loopy ball around off, pushed towards the cover region.
On the pads, kept out.
Floated around off, Taijul keeps it out.
FOUR! Poor from Cornwall. Easy boundary given away. Short and wide outside off Taijul cuts it through backward point and bags a boundary.
Flat and on middle and leg, clipped through square leg for an easy single.
Beaten! Lovely from Gabriel! A shortish length and just outside off, Taijul pokes at it away from his body to get beaten.

Dropped! That should've been taken. Gabriel is not pleased one bit. Simplest of catches and Windies' skipper makes the mess of it.  Fuller and on middle, Taijul flicks it straight to Brathwaite at mid-wicket who drops the sitter.
Shortish and just around off, Taijul defends it out.
Quick run! Good length and around off and middle, it is pushed to mid on. The mid-wicket fielder it slow to get to the ball and they see the chance of taking the single. Make it easily in the end.
In the channel outside off, Jayed lets it be.
Jayed keeps out the last ball of the over. A good length ball around off, he pushes it towards the cover region. He wants the run but Taijul is clearly not keen.

Tossed up and on middle, Taijul looks to go big on the leg side but ends up gettig an inside edge. It goes to deep square leg. They take one. Think for the second but it is not on. So, Cornwall gets 5 ball to bowl at the number 11 batsman.

Floated outside off, Jayed look to defend. It goes off the outer half, wide of the first slip fielder. They go for the run. Blackwood from the first slip position gets to the ball and fires the throw at the non-striker's end.
On middle, Taijul goes for the slog again. Mistimes it but manages to hit it wide of mid on. Two taken.
Flat and around middle, tucked on the leg side.

Is that another drop? Cornwall thinks so. Tossed up and outside off, Taijul looks to hit it over covers but is beaten. Da Silva, the keeper, fumbles behind. Replays later rolled in and it showed it did hit he bat.
Loopy and on middle, played back to Cornwall. So, Gabriel gets 6 balls at Jayed.
Slips the first one down the leg side. Jayed misses his flick.
Good length and just outside off, Jayed keeps it out.
WIDE! A Sharp bouncer from Joseph. Jayed does well to move out of the way. Wided by the umpire.

Big appeal for LBW but turned down. They are not even thinking about the review. This one is angled in from middle, Jayed looks to work it on the leg side but misses. That clearly looked high and going down the leg side. Well, well. A late call from West Indies for the DRS. Not gonna help though as Ultra Edge detects a big inside edge.
Outside off, left alone.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jayed cannot keep this sharp bouncer out. Superb from Joseph. A snortner from him. It is aimed at the body. Jayed tries to fend it off but it flies off the gloves. It goes to gully where Bonner takes a good low catch. Bangladesh have been bundled out for 296.
Tossed up and wide outside off to begin from Taijul. Brathwaite lets it go to the keeper.
Gets closer to the off pole. Brathwaite comes forward and bunts it on the off side.
FOUR! Brathwaite is up and running. A short ball from Taijul. It is on middle, Brathwaite is quick to jump on his back foot. He pulls it hard through mid-wicket to open his account.
Darted outside off, left alone.
Loopy and just around off, Kraigg is solid in defense this time.
Quicker one again from Taijul but it is once again outside off. Brathwaite has no issues leaving it alone.
Short ball and around off and middle, Campbell looks to pull but ends up getting an inside edge on the pad.
Campbell is up and running. Short and around off, turns away sharply. Campbell punches it through the covers for one to open his account.
Short again. Punched to deep cover for a run by Brathwaite.
Flat and just outside off, punched to mid off for nothing.
Quicker one around middle, clipped past the man at mid on for a quick single.
Around off, slightly short. Brathwaite bunts it past the man at short leg.
Flat and around middle, Campbell tucks it towards square leg.
Fired on the pads, Campbell this time flicks it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Floated outside off, poked towards backward point.
Short and wide outside off, slapped to deep cover for one.
Short and outside off, spinning in. Pushed to mid on off the back foot for another easy run.
Full and around off, kept out off the front foot by Kraigg.
Flat and on middle and leg, Campbell flicks it to deep square leg for an easy run.
Full and on middle, Brathwaite flicks but finds mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! Excellent review from Bangladesh and a sharp catch down the leg side from Das. That is the end of Brathwaite. That was a poor ball. It pitched on middle and spun in sharply. Brathwaite rocked back and looks to help it down to the leg side via a pull. Das was quick to move to his left to gobble up the chance. They appeal but nothing from the umpire. Das is absolutely sure that there was bat. He asks for a review. The Bangladesh skipper goes with his keeper. One replay and it is enough as Ultra Edge shows a spike off the glove.
Floated full and around off, kept out.
Moseley is off the mark. A full ball on middle and leg, he flicks it wide of mid on for one.
Short and wide outside off, Campbell punches it to deep cover for one. End of a successful over from Nayeem.
Very full and just around off, Campbell keeps it out.
Flat and on middle, clipped past the man at short leg.
Around off, shortish as well. Campbell blocks.
Quicker one! It came back in sharply after pitching around off. Extra bounce too. Campbell goes back and blocks.
Floated on middle, flicked to mid-wicket this time.
A maiden over! The last ball is fired on the pad. John blocks off his back foot.
Floated just outside off, poked towards backward point.
On middle and leg, a bit shortish in length. Moseley goes back and clips it through mid-wicket for easy two.
Floated around off, Shayne comes on the front foot to block.
Looped up and outside off, Moseley is solid in defense.
Tossed up again, this one is just outside off, Moseley comes on the front foot and pokes it towards point.
Darted short and just outside off, punched to deep cover for a single.

Huge appeal for LBW but turned down. No review this time. This was tossed up and wide outside off, Moseley goes for the drive but the ball spins in. Hits his pad. An appeal but nothing fro the umpire.
Darted outside off, left alone.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Fuller and on middle, Shayne comes down the track and whips it wide of the man at mid on. The fielder, Rahim, runs to his left and stops with his foot. They take two.
Tossed up and outside off, driven wide of the cover fielder. Mehidy there dives to his right and makes a stop. A single this time.
Flat and just outside off, punched back to the bowler.
Lovely from Nayeem. Pitches this just around off and makes it to go away. Moseley comes on the front foot and looks to defend but the ball goes past the outside edge.

Another appeal for LBW but once again they are not going for the review. Not sure if this was for LBW or for a catch. Pitches on middle and leg and goes straight. It was the arm ball from Nayeem. Mosely fails to get bat on ball. It hits his pad and goes to Sarkar at first slip who takes the catch. They appeal but nothing from the umpire. They do not go for the review.
Flat and on middle, clipped on the leg side.
Floated outside off, poked towards backward point.
Quicker one this time! It is a bit short too. Moseley does well to bring his bat down in time to defend.
Another one that spins away to beat the bat. Shortish and just outside off, Shayne gets on his back foot and looks to cut but misses. Das fumbles but catches on the second attempt. No bat though.
Tossed up and outside off, driven towards the cover region. They wanted the single but the fielder was quick to get to the ball.
Floated outside off, dabbed wide of backward point for an easy single this time.

OUT! TAKEN! 100th Test wicket for Mehidy. Quickest and youngest Bangladeshi bowler to do so. Lovely from him in his first over. Tossed up wide outside off, Moseley has a poke away from his body. He ends up getting an outside edge. Mithun at second slip makes no mistake. The match and series keeps getting better for Mehidy. Just 24 Tests to get to 100 Test wickets, quicker than the likes of Taijul Islam, Shakib Al Hasan and Mohammad Rafique. What a moment for him.
Flat and around middle, Bonner looks to work it on the leg side but the ball takes the outside edge and goes to third man. Bonner gets off the makr with a brace.
Flat and on middle, kept out.
Shorter and on middle and leg, squirted to square leg. Superb first over from Mehidy.
Floated on middle and leg, kept out.
Loopy and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off, punched down to deep cover for an easy single.
Flat and around off, Bonner stays back to block.
Full and on middle, flicked to square leg for nothing.
Shortish and on middle, Bonner goes back to block.
Flat and around off, John keeps it out.
Tossed up and just outside off, Campbell comes on the front foot to defend but the ball turns away just a hint to beat the outisde edge.
Darted outside off, it is left alone this time.
Short and on middle, it is pulled to deep mid-wicket for one. Not off the middle of the bat.
Tossed up and outside off, driven to the cover fielder. A dot.

FOUR! A welcome boundary for West Indies. A fuller ball on the pads, Bonner whips it through mid-wicket. The man in the ring dived to his right but the ball was away from his reach. The deep square leg fielder tries to get around, running to his left. Puts in a dive but fails to stop the boundary.
On off, kept out.
On the pads, Campbell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pad.
Flat and just outside off, punched towards mid off for nothing.
Short and wide outside off, Campbell fails to punish it as he mistimes the punch straight to the cover fielder.
Quicker and shorter. Punched wide of mid on for an easy run.
Sharp spin from outside off. It is pithced a bit short. Spins in as Bonner looks to work it on the leg side. Misses to get hit high on the pad.
Play and a miss! Lovely loop from Mehidy. He tosses it up and outside off, Campbell goes for the slog on the leg side. Misses to connect.
Darted quick and short on middle and leg. John is on the back foot to push it towards mid on.

NOT OUT! Campbell has just managed to drag his bat. Floated on middle, Campbell pushes it towards mid on and calls for a single. Rahim quickly gets to the ball and scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end. The ball hits the pad and goes to covers. They take one for the overthrow. The third umpire has been called for. Campbell has not dragged his bat in spite of making it well inside the crease. However, he puts the bat down just in time to survive. Poor technique from him there and it would've cost him his wicket.
Quicker one! It is on the pad. Campbell does well to get his back down in time to block.
Loopy and just around off, Campbell looks to work it on the leg side but ends up getting a soft leading edge back to the bowler.
Another soft leading edge. This one goes to cover as Campbell fails to work it on the leg side. An eventful over ends.
Flat and around middle, pushed to mid on.
Floated around off, Bonner pushes it back to the bowler.
Shortish and around off, Bonner keeps it out.
Flat and around off, Bonner stays back to block.

Appeal for a catch but not out says the umpire. It was quicker and shorter. Spins in. Bonner looks to pull but misses. The leg gully fielder takes the catch and they appeal. The umpire is not interested. Neither are Bangladesh as they do not go for the review.
Tossed up and around off. Bonner is on the front foot to block it towards the bowler.
Full and around off, Campbell comes on the front foot to block.
Short and on middle, Campbell pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket and takes two.
Full and on middle, pushed wide of mid on for a quick run.
Very full and just outside off, Bonner flicks it to deep mid-wicket for one.
On off, Campbell comes on the front foot to block.
Flat and outside off, left alone. Campbell practices the cut after the ball goes past him.
Tossed up and outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Sharp turn! This one is pitched outside off, it comes in. Bonner does well to keep it out.
On the pads, flicked through mid-wicket, past Rahim for one. He should've done better there.
Quicker one! Keeps low as well. It is around off. Campbell does well to block.

Turn again. Not big one but it is good enough to beat the outside edge this time and beats the outside edge. It is once again tossed up and around off, Campbell comes on the front foot and pokes at it with hard hands. The ball spins away just a touch to beat the outside edge.
Drags it short and just outside off, punched to deep cover for one. West Indies now lead by 150.
Flat and around off, kept out.
Short and outside off, Campbell moves across the off side and pokes it past the slip fielder. Easy two.
Big turn once again. Pitches outside off and turns in sharply. Campbell looks to defend but the ball takes an inside edge on the pad.

OUT! TIMBER! Oh, dear! What a terrible way to get out. Campbell is shocked as he stands his ground. But Bangladesh are celebrating. Campbell has to go. Very unfortunate way to get out. It was once again the quicker one from Taijul. Campbell went back to defend. He does that but the ball bounces and goes behind to take the bails off. Campbell has no idea where the ball is. To his dismay, it has clipped the bails. He is shell shocked as he stands his ground. He realizes what has happened as Bangladesh celebrate the third wicket. He goes off now, slowly on his bike.
Full and on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Another fuller one. This time Warrican pushes it to mid on.
On middle, kept out.
Quicker one from Nayeem. Bonner blocks.
Short and on middle and leg. Spins down further. Bonner looks to pull but misses.
Tossed up and outside off, Bonner looks to drive but gets an inside edge on the pad. The ball lops uiipshly but there is no one close on the off side.
Flat and on middle, kept out.
Quicker one from Nayeem. Bonner blocks. Testing over from Nayeem.
Full and on middle, Warrican pushes it to mid on and gets to the other end.
Floated around off, played back to the bowler calmly.
Very full and around off, Bonner is solid in defense this time.
Full and on middle, kept out.
On off and middle, played back to the bowler.
On middle, Bonner comes on the front foot to dead bats it.
Flat and around off, Warrican keeps it out.
Looped up and outside off, Warrican goes for the drive this time. It goes to mid-wicket off the inner half.
A solid front foot defense this time.
Flat and around off, kept out watchfully.
Floated on middle, Warrican defends it nicely.
Was that a chance? Loopy ball and outside off, Warrican looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge. A single as it goes past Sarkar at first slip.
Very full and around off, Jomel is on the front foot to defend.
Full again, Warrican keeps it out nicely.
Tossed up and around off, Warrican is once again solid in defense. Comes on the front foot and bunts it towards the silly point fielder.
Loopy and on middle, plays it back to the bowler this time.
Mild LBW appeal! This one is pitched on the pads, Warrican misses his flick and gets hit on the pad. An appeal but nothing from the umpire. It was clearly going down.
Loopy and around middle, Warrican calmly plays it to mid on for nothing to see off the over. With this, IT IS STUMPS ON DAY 3.
Short ball to start for Jayed and Bonner just pounces on it and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs to get Day 4 underway.
Once again it is on a shorter side as Bonner punches it through covers to get a couple more.
Fuller this time and Bonner defends it out off the back foot.
Jayed now bowls around the legs and Bonner clips it through square leg and runs for a couple.
Length and around middle, Bonner defends it from within the crease.

Length and around off, Bonner pushes it to cover-point and takes off for a single but Warrican was slow to begin. The fielder there hares at the ball but fails to pick up thus allowing Warrican to make his ground safely.
Fuller and spinning away from Bonner, he leaves it.
Another one which is bowled outside off, Bonner does not play at it.
Floated around off, Bonner taps it to the off side now.
On off, Bonner pushes it to straightish mid off.
Floated on off, Bonner keeps it out from within the crease.
Floated on off, Bonner pushes it to covers.
Fuller and around off, Warrican blocks it out from within the crease.
Lovely bowling. Full and in that channel around off. Jayed tempts Warrican to go for the drive and Jomel obliges. He though is not to the pitch of the ball as he gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length and around off, Warrican plays it from the crease to covers.
Once again the ball is bowled at around middle, Warrican is happy to defend it out.
Short of good length and outside off, Warrican hops and blocks it out.
! Full and outside off, Warrican makes leaves the ball for Das to collect it.
Full and darted on off, Bonner comes on the front foot and then taps it to point.
Tossed up around off, Bonner is happy to defend it out off the front foot.
Another floated ball around off, Bonner blocks it out off the front foot.
Fuller on off, driven to covers.
Flatter and around off, Bonner punches it through point and gets a brace. 50-up for West Indies
Flatter and on off, Bonner stands tall and then blocks it out.

OUT! Jayed draws the blood on Day 4! That was a beauty. He bowls the ball a bit fuller and Warrican was on the back foot as he looks to defend it out. He though gets beaten due to the inswing on the ball and gets rapped on the pads. Jayed and the slip cordon goes up in an appeal. The umpire thinks for a while before lifiting his finger. Warrican discusses with his partner but then walks off.
FOUR! Straight out of the screws! Short of a length ball around off, Mayers hangs on the back foot and then pulls it towards wide long on to get going with a boundary.
Length and around off, Mayers plays it to the leg side.
Length and around off, Mayers lets it go through.
Good length and outside off, Mayers initially looks to leave the ball but is late into it as the ball takes the toe-end of the bat and goes to point. No run taken.

An appeal and some excitement from Jayed and Das. Fuller and around off, Mayers looks to defend it out off the back foot but the ball moves away a hint to go past the outside edge. Jayed and Das are excited but not confident as Mominul says no for the review. Replays show that had he reviewed  Mayers would have been a goner as the Ultra Edge showed spike there.
Floated around off, Bonner defends it out.
Outside off, left alone by Bonner.
Fuller on off, pushed to the off side.
Floated around off, Bonner keeps it out.
Full on the stumps, Bonner looks to defend it but ekes out and inside edge past the leg pole. The ball goes to the fine leg region as the batsmen take  a single.
Full and on off, pushed to the off side.
Length ball around off, Bonner defends it out.
Another length delivery and around off, Bonner pushes it off the front foot.
On off, Bonner is solid in defense.

EDGY FOUR! Full and around off, Bonner pushes at it away from his body but the ball just about moves away to catch the outside edge and fly past the diving gullly fielder and into the fence at third man for a boundary.
Length and around leg, Bonner defends it out to the leg side.
Length ball around off, Bonner pushes it to covers for a single.
Floated on off, kept out from within the crease.
Fuller and around off, driven down through covers for a single.
Tossed up around off, Bonner pushes it to covers.
Spin and bounce! Tossed up outside off, Bonner looks to drive through the off side but is beaten by the extra bounce and turn there. The keeper does well to collect it out.
Flatter and around off, Bonner rocks onto the back foot and then punches it through covers for a single.
Floated around off, Mayers comes on the front foot and then defends it.
Length and around middle and leg, Bonner defends it to the leg side.
Low full toss around off, Bonner can only stroke it to mid off.
Fuller and around off, Bonner taps it to covers.
Nicely defended. Fuller and around off, Bonner comes right behind the line of the ball as he defends it.
Right on the target from Jayed as Bonner defends it out towards covers.
Short of good length and around off, Bonner taps it to cover-point.
Fuller and pushed on off, Mayers defends it out to the off side from the crease.
Floated around off, Mayers once again keeps it ball out from the crease.
Darted on middle, turned away towards mid-wicket.
Another fuller one on midlde, pushed back to the bowler.
Flighted around off, Mayers defends it to the off side with soft hands.
Fuller and around off, Mayers strokes this ball to point and scampers for a single.

OUT! UMPIRE's CALL ON HITTING THE WICKETS! Jayed and Das both will be relieved. Lovely bowling from Jayed. He lands one around off and gets the ball to come into Mayers. Kyle is on the back foot as he looks to defend it. He misses it and gets rapped on the pads. An appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Mayers reviews it straightaway. Replays come in and it is a flat line on Ultra Edge as the Ball Tracker shows it is Umpire's Call on hitting the wickets. Mayers is gone and West Indies are 5 down.
Length and around off, Blackwood strokes it to mid off.
Good length and around off, pushed to the off side.
SIX! Clobbered away! Length and around off, Blackwood gets into the position as he lifts it over the long on boundary to get a maximum.
Full and around off, Jermaine chips it to covers but it falls short of the fielder there.
Length and around off, clipped towards square leg for a single.
On off, Blackwood pushes it to covers.
Flatter outside off, Blackwood punches it to deep cover for a single. The umpire checks the danger area again.
Tossed up outside off, left alone.
Flighted around off, Bonner defends it out off the front foot.
Fuller and around off, Bonner strokes it to covers off the front foot.
Tossed up on leg, turned away towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length and outside off, Bonner is happy to leave it alone.
Fuller and around off, Bonner defends it out off the front foot.
Calculated leave! Length and around off, slightly coming into Bonner, Nkrumah watches the ball closely as he makes a leave.
Length ball around off, Bonner taps it to cover-point. He played that away from the body. A single taken.
Full on off, Blackwood drives it down to wide long on for a single.
On a length and around middle, clipped towards mid-wicket,
Floated around off, Blackwood goes for a wild drive but is nowhere to the pitch of the ball as he misses it.

OUT! STUMPED! Sharp work from Das there! Taijul is a smart bowler. He saw Blackwood looking to take him on on the previous ball. He once again tosses it up and Blackwood goes for the drive. He tries his best to get to the pitch of the ball but the ball moves away from him. Das collects it and whips the bails off in a lightning speed. The third umpire is aked for help as the replays come in. There is no part of the foot behind the line and Jermaine has to walk back to the hut.
Tossed up and around off, Joshua goes to defend it but is beaten by the turn. Lovely bowling from Taijul.
On off, kept out.
Flat and full outside off, Joshua dead bats it.
On midlde, pushed off the back foot. A wicket-maiden for Taijul.
Tossed up around off, pushed to covers.
Darted down leg, Bonner makes a leave.
On middle, Bonner keeps it out off the back foot.
Tossed up ball around middle, turned away towards square leg.
On leg, turned out to the leg side.

On middle, Bonner looks to turn it to the leg side but the ball hits him on the thigh. Bangladesh have taken the review as they are claiming a catch. The replays roll in and it clearly show daylight when the ball passes the bat. So Bonner stays to fight it out for the Men in Maroon.
Floated outside off, Joshua gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tosssed up outside off, Joshua makes a leave.
Loopy on off, Joshua defends it out.
FOUR! swept away! Full and around middle, Da Silva sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Flatter on middle, whipped away towards long on for a single.
Floated outside off once again, Bonner goes for the push but is beaten once again.
Tossed up on leg, tiucked away towards mid-wicket.
Floated on middle, turned to short leg by Joshua.
Flighted around off, Joshua dead bats it.
On off, kept out by Joshua.
Spinning into Joshua, Da Silva lets the ball thud into his thigh pads.
On middle and leg, Joshua once again allows the ball to hit him on the thigh pad.
Tossed up on off, quicker too as Bonner pushes it hastily to silly point.
Angling into Bonner, Nkrumah goes for the sweep but he gets beaten. The keeper whips the bails off but Bonner's back foot was going nowhere.
Pushed through on off, Bonner defends it out.
Quicker and on off, Bonner keeps it out off the back foot.
Flatter on off, pushed through covers for a single.
On off, Joshua defends it out.
Tosed up on off, Bonner comes on the front foot and then turns it to mid-wicket.
Around middle, blocked out off the front foot.
Flatter and turning into Joshua, Da Silva turns it to short leg.
Another flatter one on leg, Joshua tucks it to short leg.
Four! Pressure released! Tossed up and in the slot for Joshua to slog it away towards deep mid-wicket and the ball crosses the fence there for a boundary.
Tossed up on leg, Joshua clips it to wide long on for a single.

What about the drift and turn along with the bounce there. Lovely bowling from Taijul. Floats one on off, Joshua looks to defend it out but the extra bounce on it means the ball takes the outside edge but it falls short and wide of the slips.
Darted in off, Joshua comes on the front foot to defend but ekes out an inside edge there.
Flatter on off, slapped away towards covers for a single.
Turn for Taijul there as he floats one around off, Bonner looks to defend it but is beaten.
Full on off, Bonner dead bats it this time.
On middle, Bonner is happy to defend it.
FOUR! Welcome to the attack once again says Joshua. Overpitched around off, Da Silva leans into the drive and creams it through covers as the ball crosses the fence there. The lead is now 203 runs!
Length and around off, Joshua defends it to covers.
FOUR! Clipped away! That is a freebie from Jayed. Full and on the pads, Joshua flicks it uppishly and towards deep square leg fence to fetch a boundary. Useful runs for West Indies.
Length and around off, Da Silva taps it to point.
Good length and around off, Joshua pushes it to point.
Good length and outside off, Joshua makes a leave. 8 runs off the over.
Fuller on off, Bonner drives it straight to covers.
Loopy and outside off, Bonner leaves it alone.

Joshua is safe! Full and around of,f Bonner taps it to covers and hares for a quick single. Najmul Hossain Shanto gets to the ball and releases the through to Das who takes the bails off. The third umpire is called for and the replays show that Joshua was well inside when the bails were dislodged.
On off, defended off the front foot.
Flatter on off, pushed through to the off side for a single.
Tossed up on off, kept out by Bonner.
Full around off, Joshua plays it of the back foot and from within the crease.
Full and around off, Da Silva drives it to mid off.
Length and around off, Joshua taps it to covers off the back foot.
Another fuller one around off, Joshua stays inside his crease as he strokes it to covers.
Easy leave there for Joshua as the line from Jayed is well outside off.
Full and targetting the stumps, Joshua is on the back foot as he defends it by coming right behind the line of the ball. A maiden from Jayed.
Pushed through on off, Bonner pushes it to the bowler off the back foot.
On middle, Bonner works it to mid on.
Flatter and on leg, Bonner turns it to short fine leg.
Tossed up on off, Bonner is a bit squared up as he defends it out to the off side.

Lovely bowling from Hasan. Tossed up and a bit quicker on middle, Bonner looks to play it off the back foot but inside edges it onto his boots. The ball is not far from rolling onto the stumos as it rolls away past the poles.
On middle, defended out. A testing over from Mehidy Hasan.
Length and on middle, turned away towards mid-wicket.
Full and around middle, Joshua drives it down the ground but the man from mid on moves to his left to field it.
Length and around off, Da Silva pushes it to point. Joshua is batting outside his crease to cater to the reverse swing.
Full and outside off, Joshua watches the ball and then makes a leave by lifitng his willow.
Full an in the slot for Joshua to play the on drive. He though fails to nail  it in the gap as the ball goes to the fielder at mid on.
Good length and around off, Joshua is happy to play out the over by tapping the last ball to point. West Indies have slowed down considerably since the wicket of Blackwood.

Another quick single! Tossed up on middle, Bonner clips it to short mid-wicket as he takes off for a single. The fielder there throws the ball to the keeper who whips the bails off but Joshua was well in.
Full on off, clipped to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on leg, Joshua pushes it to short leg.
Full on middle, Joshua strokes it to the right of the bowler who fields it.
On middle, Joshua turns it away to square leg.
Flatter on middle, defended off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, blocked out by Bonner.
Flatter around off, defended off the back foot this time.
Fuller around off, driven to sweeper cover for a single.
pushed down to mid off.
Tossed up on off, Joshua defend it right near his boots.
Floated outside off, Joshua leaves it alone. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Tossed up on leg, going down leg too, Bonner makes a leave. The ball though takes the thigh pad and runs to the fime leg region. The batsmen don't run.
FOUR! pulled away! Flatter and around middle, Bonner rocks on the back foot and then pulls it past the square leg fielder for a boundary. 100 comes up for West Indies.
On middle, blocked out by Bonner.
Tossed up on middle, turned away towards the leg side.
Tossed up on leg, spinning down too as Bonner looks to lay bat on ball but is beaten.
On middle, driven down to long on for a single.
Tossed up on off, Bonner comes on the front foot to defend it out.
Flatter and around off, Bonner goes on the back foot as he punches it to sweeper cover for a single.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Taijul is just too hot to handle when he is on song. Nicely looped up ball around off, Joshua is drawn forward to defend it out but the ball  grips and turns to catch the outside edge of Da Silva's bat. Soumya Sarkar at first slip accepts the ball gleefully.
On off, pushed down to long on for a single. Joseph is off the mark here.
Floated on off, defended to silly point.
Floated around middle, turned away towards mid-wicket. A successful over from Taijul comes to an end. two runs and an all-important wicket of Joshua Da Silva in it.
Fuller on off, Joseph drives it down the ground towards long on as he takes a couple of runs.
Tossed up on off, Joseph looks to drive but keeps it a bit uppish as the Nayeem there goes to his right to catch but the ball falls short of him.
Tossed up on middle, Alzarri plays it right near his boots.
Floated on off, Joseph is solid in defense.
Another tossed up ball from Nayeem and Joseph plays it off the front foot.
SIX! Hammered! Full and in the slot for Joseph slogs it high and over the deep mid-wicket fence for half a dozen.
On off, pushed to covers for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Joseph comes and goes quickly! Lovely bowling from Taijul as he gives this one a lot more air and tosses it up around off, Joseph looks to turn it to the leg side but ends up closing the bat face early to eke out a leading edge what deflects of silly point and lobs to covers where Najmul Hossain Shanto takes the catch,

Floated on off, Cornwall looks to go downtown but ends up chipping it hig and towards extra cover. The fielder from mid off goes for the catch but the ball falls into the no man's land as the single is taken.
On off, pushed to covers for a single.
Floated on off, Cornwall defends it out.
On off, kept out.

OUT! CASTLED! That was an indicreet shot from the man who has played well so far. Maybe he was looking to score a few quick runs as he was running out of partners. Nayeem tosses one up and gets it to spin into Bonner who looks to play the reverse sweep. He though is not in a position to play at it as the ball sneaks through his legs and crashes into the wickets behind.
Floated on off, defended off the front foot.
On middle, clipped towards square leg for a single.
Full on off, kept out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Good catch from Rahim in the deep. That is all from West Indies as they end on 117 runs. Floated on off, Cornwall goes for the slog but cannot middle it off the bat. The ball goes high and towards deep mid-wicket where Mushfiqur Rahim near the ropes takes a brilliant catch.
Full on off, defended by Tamim.
Another fuller one on off, Tamim keeps it out.
Full on off, pushed down to long off as Tamim gets off the mark with a single.
Tossed up around off, tapped towards covers.
Outside off, left alone.
On the pads, clipped to fine leg for a brace.
FOUR! That should give confidence to Iqbal. Full and around off, Tamim plays it late as he guides it through the gully region and into the fence for a boundary.
On the pads, flicked away towards square leg for a couple of runs.
Another two runs as Tamim pushes it off the inner half towards mid-wicket.
Short and around middle, Tamim ducks under it.
On off, kept out.
Length ball outside off, left alone.
Tossed up outside off, Sarkar leaves it alone.
Floated on off, Sarkar keeps it out off the front foot.
On the pads, pushed down to long off for a single. Sarkar is off the mark.
On the hips, clipped to the leg side for a single.
Flatter and on off, defended to the off side.
Flat and outside off, Sarkar lets it be.
FOUR! Delightful stroke! Full and outside off, Tamim frees his arms and strokes it through cover-point and the ball goes to the fence in no time.
! Joseph is leaking runs here. Full on the pads this time and Tamim clips it through backward square leg and gets a boundary again. Second of the over.
Again down leg, Tamim looks to tuck but he misses it.
Length ball around off, Iqbal gets right behind the ball to defend it out.
Back of a length and outside off, Iqbal plays it to the off side.
Good shot for no runs. Full and outside off, Tamim drives but the fielder at covers does well to field it.
FOUR! Now Sarkar Joins the party. Tossed up around off, Sarkar skips down the track and lofts it over covers for a couple of bounce and into the fence.
On midlde, tucked to the leg side.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Floated outside off, left alone by Sakar.
On off, Sarkar is solid in defense.
Flighted on off, defended out by Sarkar now.
Short of good length around off, Sarkar hops and fends it away to point. A single is taken.
Length and around middle, Sarkar clips it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Short of good length and around off, Sarkar dabs it point.
Short of good length around off, Sarkar defends it out to the off side.
Bumper on off and middle, Sarkar was expecting it as he sways away from it.
Sarkar is solid on the front foot as he defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off,Tamim defends it off the front foot.
clipped away towards square leg for a single.
Darting on off, pushed to short leg.
Tossed up outside off, Tamimn defends it out.
Tossed up around middle, clipped towards short mid-wicket.
Flighted on middle, tucked towards the leg side.
Fuller in length and width on offer as Tamim plays the drive but cannot beat the man at covers.
Short of good length and outside off, Tamim gets on top of the bounce and plays it to sweeper cover for a single.
Length and outside off, Sarkar has no issues in leaving this one for Joshua Da Silva.
Short of good length and on off, Sarkar taps it to cover-point and scampers for a single. Bangladesh need 200 runs to win!
Short of good length around off, Tamim drops it behind point and takes a single.
Easy runs! Short and around off, Sarkar pulls it through mid-wicket. He though does not have the timing on the shot as the ball is fielded well inside the ropes. A couple taken.
Tossed up on middle, turned towards square leg.
FOUR! Nicely done! Full and on the pads, Tamim gets down and then sweeps it fine and down to fine leg for a boundary.
Darted on middle, driven down to long on for a single by Tamim.
Tossed up around off, Sarkar defends it out to the off side.
Tossed up on middle and leg, turned away towards square leg.
Much better line this time. Tossed up on off, Sarkar blocks it out right under his eyes.
Tossed up on off, Tamim drives it inside out towards extra cover for a single.
On the pads, clipped towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller on off, defended to the off side.
FOUR! Floated on middle, Tamim lofts it towards mid-wicket and the ball goes onto meet the fence there for a boundary.

NOT OUT! Umpire's Call on hitting the wickets. Flighted on off, Tamim looks to flick it to the leg side but is beaten to get hit on the pads. The bowler appeals but the umpire is unmoved. West Indies think of reviewing it and they do so. Replays roll in Ultra Edge confirms no bat involved as Ball Tracker shows that it is Umpire's Call.
On off, turned to mid-wicket.
On off, pushed to mid-wicket.
Tossed up around off, driven down to long on for a single.
FOUR! Paddled away! 50-run stand comes up for Bangladesh after 12 innings. The openers are going great here. Tossed up on leg, Tamim paddles it fine towards fine leg to get a boundary.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, turned away to the leg side.
FOUR! Innovative hit! Tossed up and going down leg, Tamim goes for the revese sweep as he fetches it from outside leg and nails it towards deep point for a boundary.
On middlem pushed to square leg for a single.
Beautiful! Tossed up outside off, Tamim prods forward to defend but is beaten by the turn and bounce there.
Tossed up on middle, turned to mid-wicket.
Fuller on middle, played back to the bowler.
On off, blocked to the leg side .
FOUR! Punched away! Flatter and outside off, Tamim punches it off the back foot and through point for a boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! That was a brilliant bowling change. Tossed up outside off, Sarkar looks to cut it late through point but the ball takes the edge and lobs off the pads of the keeper towards first slip where Cornwall takes the catch. West Indies appeal but the umpire does not agree. West Indies take the review and replays roll in. Ultra Edge comes on and shows a clear spike. So Sarkar has to depart.
On off, pushed to covers.
Fuller on off, pushed to the bowler.
Full outside off, pushed to the off side.
On off, pushed to covers.
Full on middle and leg, blocked out. A brilliant over from the skipper.
Full on off, kept out.
Full and on middle, Tamim drives it to long on for a single.
On middle and leg, tucked to the leg side.
Fuller around off, turning into him. Najmul clips it to square leg for a single.
Full on off, Tamim pushes it to covers.
FOUR! Flicked away! Tossed up on middle, Tamim flicks it through mid-wicket and the ball races to the fence.
Darted on off, pushed to covers.
Fuller and around off, Najmul plays it to short cover.
Another tossed up ball on off, Shanto defends it to covers.
On off, blocked out.
FOUR! A freebie for Najmul. Flighted ball outside off, Hossain Shanto gets under the ball and drives it through covers as the ball goes onto meet the fence at sweeper cover.
Floated on off, defended out.
Darted on off, pushed through to long on for a single. Tamim gets to his 28th Test Fifty too. What a time to get. Can he inspire his team to a win.
On off, defended off the front foot.
On middle, clipped towards mid-wicket for no run.
Fuller on off, pushed to the bowler.
Tossed up ball on off, Najmul drives it back to the bowler once again.
Around off, defended to point.
Tossed up on off, driven to short cover.

OUT! CAUGHT! A wicket out of nowhere. Tamim stands in disbelief. A nothing shot to get out. He departs soon after getting to his fifty. West Indies fighting it out. The skipper Kraigg Brathwaite inspires them here. Tossed up ball on off, Tamim looks to play the drive but he plays it uppishly and straight to short cover where Sheyne Moseley takes a stunner. Mominul Haque replaces him in the middle.
On off, pushed to covers.
Floated on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Flighted on off, driven to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! Flatter outside off, Najmul fetches it from near the gloves of the keeper and he cuts it towards deep point for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Outside off, Haque lets it be.
Floated on off, defended to covers.
On middle, driven to covers.
On middle and leg, kept out to the leg side.
On off, kept out.
Floated on leg, tucked towards the leg side for a single.
Floated on off, pushed to mid off.
Flatter outside off, cut straight to point. A single is sneaked.
On off, Najmul blocks it out.
Another tossed up on midlde, Najmul comes on the front foot and smothers the spin on it.
Flighted around off, Shanto is well forward in defense.
Flatter outside off, slapped to point.
Tossed up on off, Haque looks to defend but ekes out an inside edge on the pads.
Flatter on off, Haque taps it to the off side off the back foot.
On off, tapped to point.
Flatter outside off, Haque slaps it to point.
On middle, defended to the off side.
Flatter outside off, slapped to covers.
Fuller on off, Najmul comes down the track and plays it to the bowler.
Looped up outside off, pushed to short cover.
Fuller on off, Najmul dead bats it.
Slower and outside off, slapped to long off for a single.
Full and outside off, driven to covers.
Full on middle, pushed to mid on.
On off, kept out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Brilliant from Brathwaite to give the ball to Cornwall. The giant man strikes. Flatter around middle, Shanto goes for the clip towards the leg side but inside edges it onto the thigh pad and the ball lobs to short leg. Sheyne Moseley takes the catch. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4!
Fuller and on off, driven back to the bowler.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Gets forward to a full ball and blocks it safely.
Short and outside off, Mominul goes back and slaps it to deep cover for a single.
Tossed up ball on the pads, tucked to square leg for one.
Extra flight, well over the eye level but it lands too full outside off and Haque drives it to deep cover for a single.
Loopy and full on off, Rahim strides forward and defends it to the off side.
Takes a couple of steps down the track and knocks it down to long on for one. Easily doing!
Gets away with a poor delivery. Short and wide outside off, Mominul cuts but finds point.
Too full and outside off, Rahim walks forward and drives it to covers where there is a misfield and they cross.
Aerial but safe! Loopy and full around off, Mominul gets forward and pushes it through the line. It's aerial but drops just in front of Brathwaite at short cover.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Haque missed out in the last over but not this time as he rocks back and whacks it through point.
Floated and full on off, Haque stretches forward and defends it to covers.
Flatter and shorter on off, Mominul goes on the back foot and blocks it down.
Fullish and on off, Mominul draws forward to defend. End of a mixed-bag over by Rahkeem.
Flighted and too full on middle, Rahim forces it down to long on for a run.
A low full toss on leg, it's flicked on the leg side but straight to mid-wicket.
Goodness me, that was close. A slider by Kraigg, landing full and close to off, it skids back in as Mominul chooses to cut. Ends up chopping it down in front of slip.
Floater this time, around leg, Haque clips it off his pads to square leg for a run.
This time it's on middle and leg for the right-hander, Rahim works it behind square leg for one.
A touch flatter on off, Mominul defends it watchfully from the crease.
Hangs on the back foot and defends it by opening the face of his bat.
Gets forward and defends it gently to mid-wicket.
Around leg, Rahim pads it away.
Presses forward to a full ball and blocks it easily.
Lunges to a full ball around off and dead-bats it to the off side.
Forces a full ball down through mid on for a single.
The batsman has played towards covers.
Rahim has just watchfully blocked this out.
Fuller and on off, Rahim stretches forward in defense.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out to the off side.
Shortish and outside off, Rahim uses the crease and cuts it to sweeper cover for two.
Shout for an lbw! Very full and around leg, Rahim fails to flick and is hit on the pads. They put in an unsuccessful appeal.
Short and around off, Mominul cuts but finds the diving point fielder.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it to the off side.
Gets on the front foot and pushes it defensively to covers.
Floated delivery, full and on off, Mominul is forward in defense.
Action replay of the last delivery. The bowler needs to try something different.
Same thing over and over again and it's the end of the over. Loopy and on off, defended to covers.
Slower through the air, landing full around leg and turning down to clip Rahim's pads. It goes past the keeper and they take a couple of leg byes.
Flighted and too full on middle, Rahim pushes it back to the bowler.
Slightly quicker and fuller on off, Rahim lunges and defends it off the inner half.
Shorter on off, skidding away, Rahim gets back and taps it down to point for a run. These two are milking runs at will.
Nicely flighted, landing too full on middle, Haque drives it back to the bowler.
Slower through the air but short outside off, Mominul cuts it straight to point.
FOUR! Fine shot! Too full in length and outside off, Rahim drives it delightfully through the gap between mid off and covers for a boundary. Sensible batting, picking their moments.
Fullish and around leg, Rahim flicks but finds short mid-wicket.
Shortish and on off, turning in, Rahim goes deep inside the crease and cuts it to point for a run.
Lunges to a full ball on off and defends it back to the bowler.
Floated full on off, Mominul pushes it off his front leg to covers.
Flatter and a touch shorter on off, Haque defends it off his back foot.
Slower through the air, full and on off, it's driven down the ground to mid off.

OUT! Caught behind! Lovely flight on this delivery as it lands full around off and turns away sharply. Rahim leans forward to defend but it spins past the outside edge and Joshua collects the ball. He appeals and the finger goes up as well. Rahim is quick to review it but the UltraEdge shows a big spike. Rahim returns shaking his head. Body blow to Bangladesh. 130 needed more.
Flighted and full around off, Mithun drives it through cover-point for a run.
A touch on the shorter side as it lands on middle, Mominul goes back and helps it behind square leg for a run.
Poor delivery, short and wide outside off, Mithun gets back and slaps it to deep cover for a run. The keeper from behind the stumps quips - 'Come on Jomel, don't try too hard!'
Strides forward and defends it from the inside half of his bat to short leg.
Flatter and on middle, Mithun goes back and defends it down.
Full and outside off, Mithun defends it by getting forward.
SIX! This is one way to tackle the spin. Mithun gives the charge to negate the spin and strikes it massively over wide long on.
Gets forward and eases it to point for a quick run.
Flatter and fuller on off, driven to mid off.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Quicker one outside off, skidding away, it's left alone by Mithun.
Bowls it a touch short and on off, Mithun hangs back and pushes it to covers. Called a no ball for overstepping.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Full and flighted on off, Mithun eases his drive down to long off for a single.
In the air... Safe! Tossed up ball on middle, Mominul uses his feet and drop kicks it over mid-wicket for a couple.
Full and outside off, defended to the off side.
Almost carries to mid on! Fuller and on middle, Haque whips it across the line and it goes on the bounce to the fielder.
Sharp turn down the leg side, Mithun allows it through.

OUT! Turn and bounce for Cornwall and another one bites the dust for Bangladesh. The big man plants this delivery around middle and it shoots up as Mithun goes on the back foot to work it away. But the ball keeps on jumping, takes the shoulder of his bat and goes to Bonner at short leg. He reacts sharply to accept the catch and Mithun stands there in disbelief. 116 needed more.
Flighted and on off, Liton goes back and somehow defends it down safely. That was also bouncing extra.
Flatter and on off, defended off the back foot.
Hangs on the back foot and defends it to the off side.
Flighted and on off, Das gets back and turns it behind square leg for a run.
Darted on leg, Das clips it to short mid-wicket.
Floated around off, some uneven bounce as Das pokes at it and gets it to point. A single taken.
Floated on off, Haque prods forward to defend it out.
Flatter on middle, Haque pushes it to the leg side.

FOUR! The skipper leading the side here. He is going about his business to keep Bangladesh in the hunt. Warrican tosses one up around off, Haque fetches from there and sweeps it all along the ground through backward square leg. The ball races to the fence there.
On middle, Haque works it towards square leg for a single.
Flighted and outside off, Mominul pads it away.
Flatter and shorter on off, Haque goes back and plays it down to point.
Uses his feet and drives a full ball down to long on for a run.
Strides forward to a full ball and clips it with the spin to deep mid-wicket for one.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it to the off side.

FOUR! Skidding down the leg side, Mominul gets back to work it around. It takes the inner half and races behind to fine leg. Blackwood gives the chase from first slip and slides near the fence to pull it back in. The umpire though wants to get it checked. The third umpire gets involved and after watching multiple angles, it's deemed to be a boundary. Blackwood's leg was in contact with the rope when he touched the ball.
Full and flighted on off, Das defends it by getting forward.
Fuller and around off, it's driven to the left of mid off for a brisk single.
Turns it off his pads to square leg and rotates the strike. That's all they need to do.
Nicely floated and full on middle, it's stroked down to long off for a run.
Quicker one, skidding down the leg side, Mominul tickles it along the ground to long leg for one.
Slower through the air, full and on off, Liton presses forward and defends it back.
Flighted and full on off, Mominul drives but finds short cover.
Too full in length and outside off, it's nicely driven through the gap at covers for a single. 98 needed more to win!
Quicker and full on middle, defended from the back foot by Das.
Full and flighted on off, Das flicks but finds short mid-wicket.
Full again, a lot slower through the air, Liton nudges it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Loopy delivery, drifting in around off, Mominul stretches forward and defends it back to his counterpart.
Flighted and around off, it's worked in front of square leg for a run. The fielder fumbles slightly and allows the second run as well.
Allows the ball to turn back in and taps it down towards backward short leg.
Short and on off, some extra bounce, Liton goes back and cuts it through point. Controlled the bounce well.
Slower through the air, full and on middle, Mominul defends it back.
Quicker and fuller outside off, Haque lunges to defend and does so by taking the bottom hand away.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it to the off side.
Looped up ball around middle, Das defends it out.
Fuller around off, Das makes room and drives it to covers.
Flatter and outside off, Das slaps it off the back foot towards deep point and takes a couple.
Much better! Tosses one up around off, Das looks to defend it off the front foot. The ball though spins past his outside edge on this occasion.
Flatter once again and outside off, Das cuts it to point.
Fuller and on middle, Das defends it out. Warrican has overstepped and it is called a no ball.
Fuller and around off, Das drives but the fielder at covers does well to stop it.
Haque does not offer a stroke.
Angled onto the pads now, Haque clips to square leg for a run.
Floated on middle, turned away towards short leg.
Another floater on middle, Das clips it past leg gully and towards fine leg for a couple of runs.
Another delivery which is bowled on the leg stump, Das rocks on the back foot and turns it past leg gully for another two runs.
Full on middle, clipped to the leg side for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Once again the close-in fielder coming into play. Warrican is into the act again. He tosses this one up around off and gets it to spin into Mominul. Haque is half-forward as he looks to defend it. The ball though takes the inside edge and goes off the pads to Cornwall who takes a dolly at leg gully.
Very full around leg, driven back to the bowler.
Full and around off, Hasan pushes it off the front foot to covers.
Tossed up on off, slapped to point.
Flatter and outside off, Mehidy cuts but finds the fielder at point.
On the pads, clipped to mid-wicket. Another successful over for West Indies as they get closer to winning this Test.
On middle and leg, Das clips it towards mid-wicket and gets to the other end with a single.
Tossed up on off, Mehidy plays it to mid on.
Mehidy runs it on the bounce to slips.
On middle, Hasan turns it to mid-wicket.
Fuller on middle, Mehidy sweeps but hits short leg on the way. The ball rolls to the side of the pitch.
Tossed up and spinning in with the angle, Mehidy looks to defend but misses to get hit high on the thigh pad.
Full on middle, clipped to backward square leg for a single.
On the pads this time, Mehidy turns it to the leg side and gets a single. 150 up for Bangladesh, 81 needed more.
Floated on middle and leg, Das presses forward in defense.
Flighted and around leg, tucked away to the leg side.
Flatter and on off, punched off the back foot towards covers for a single.

NOT OUT! Clear daylight. Quicker and pushed through on off, Das prods forward to defend but the ball spins away to beat the outside edge. The keeper collects and shows disappointment initially and then they decide to review it. The replays come on and the Ultra Edge shows no spike. Das survives.
Flighted and full on off, it's whipped to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.

OUT! Fantastic reaction catch from the keeper! Cornwall bags yet another wicket in this Test match, his 8th overall. Short and wide outside off, there to be cut and Liton tries to do that. But there is extra bounce and it catches the outside edge. Joshua hangs onto the catch and West Indies are over the moon. Three wickets more to make it 2-0.
Tossed up on off, kept out by Taijul.
Slanting on the pads, Taijul looks to tuck it to the leg side but the ball takes the thigh pad and drops near the pitch on the leg side.
Taijul is off the mark. Tossed up on leg. This time he flicks it towards fine leg and gets a brace.
On off, Taijul pushes it through covers for a single.
Flatter outside off, pushed to the mid on region.
On off, slapped to point but not in the gap.
Shorter and around off, kept out off the back foot.
On middle, turned towards square leg for a single.
Fuller on middle, pushed to covers.
On off and middle, Mehidy is happy to defend this one out.
Full outside off, pushed to covers.
On off and middle, Taijul dead-bats it.
On middle and leg, turned away towards mid-wicket.
Fuller and around off, Taijul drives it to covers.
Anther fuller and outside off ball, Taijul plays it to covers.
Flatter and around off, Taijul stands tall to defend it out. Maiden!
Sliding on leg, Mehidy turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Full and outside off, Taijul plays it back to Warrican.
On middle, tucked to short leg.
Fuller and outside off, Taijul taps it to point with an open face.
Tossed up outside off, pushed to the fielder on the off side.
On middle, solidly defended by Taijul.
Darted on leg, clipped towards square leg for a single.
Tossed up and on off, Taijul smothers the spin on it as he jams it down.
That was close to shaving the leg pole. Fuller and around off, Taijul goes for the drive but ekes out an inside edge which runs past the leg pole and towards fine leg. A brace taken.
On off, played to covers.
Flatter and around off, Taijul cuts it in front of point and gets a couple now.
Flatter and outside off, Taijul decides to leave it this time. 68 needed more with a minimum of 7 overs left in the day.
Looped up ball on middle, Mehidy defends it off the back foot.
Floated on off, driven back to the bowler.
Flatter and around off, Mehidy cuts it off the back foot but straight to point.
Floated on off, pushed to wide mid off.
Tossed up and angled on off, defended out.

NOT OUT! Mehidy Hasan is glued to his crease when the bails come off. Lovely piece of bowling. Warrican tosses one up around off, as Mehidy Hasan goes for the big slog sweep. He though  fails to get any connection as the keeper cvollects it and whips the bails off. The third umpire is called for as the replays come in. The replays show that he is safe when the bails are whipped off.

OUT! Taijul departs, given lbw! Cornwall delivers a flighted ball around off, it's a slider, Taijul tries to defend without much front foot movement, playing for the non-existent spin. He is pinged on the front pad, they appeal and the umpire agrees. Taijul takes the DRS but the UltraEdge finds no inside edge and the Ball Tracker shows three reds. All adjacent, Cornwall has 9 in the match.

That would have hurt! Tossed up ball on middle, spinning in, Nayeem tries to defend but misses. It hits the higher part of his front pad and lobs up to hit the batsman on the chin. Nayeem is in pain. He isn't wearing the helmet.
Goes on the back foot to work it on the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Quicker and fuller on middle, pushed down to mid on.
Turning back into the batsman from the fuller length, Nayeem tries to defend but gets it away off the inner edge.
Fetches a full ball from outside off and sweeps it fine down the leg side. Gabriel stops it with his boot near the fence and saves two.
Floated on leg, turned away towards mid-wicket for a couple.
Tossed up around off, Nayeem goes for a flick towards the leg side but ends up getting a leading edge which rolls to the point fielder.
Flatter and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up around off, Nayeem plays it to the bowler.
Flighted on off, clipped to square leg for a single.
On off, kept out off the front foot.
Flatter and around middle and leg, turned away towards square leg for a single.
Flighted around off, pushed down to mid on.
On off, Mehidy presses forward in defense.
Flatter and turning into leg, Mehidy turns it to square leg for a single.
Darted around off, Nayeem gets his bat down late to push it to point.
On the pads of Mehidy, clipped away towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Well struck! A brave shot to play at this stage. Floated around off, Nayeem gets down and sweeps it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary. 55 needed more.
On off, pushed to the long off region for a single.
On middle, pushed to covers.
Tossed up on middle, Mehidy looks to tuck it to the leg side but ends up getting a soft leading edge to the off side.
Flatter and outside off, punched to the off side at the last moment off the back foot.
On off, pushed to covers.
Tossed up ball on off, Nayeem keeps his bat and pad together to defend it out.
On middle, swept towards square leg for a single.
Flatter and around off, the ball sticks into the surface a bit as Mehidy keeps it out off the back foot.
Full and on off, driven down to long on for a single.
Flatter and around off, Nayeem hops a bit to defend it out.
On off, kept out to covers safely.
FOUR BYES! Poor stuff from Kraigg. Tossed up and going down leg, Mehidy misses his flick and the keeper too fails to collect it. The ball goes to the fine leg fence.
FOUR BYES! And Brathwaite once again drifts one down leg and Joshua Da Silva fails to collect one. The ball goes to the fine leg fence for four byes. 8 runs gifted, really poor from West Indies!
Tossed up on leg, tucked to the leg side for a single.

OUT! THREE REDS! Tossed up and around leg, Nayeem thinks it has landed outside leg and hence offers no shot to take it on his pads. The West Indian players appeal and the finger has gone up. Nayeem opts for the review straightaway. The Ball Tracker shows that it has pitched just inside the line of the leg stump and is going on to disturb the stumps. Nayeem has to walk back. Kraigg is jumping in celebration.
Floated on off, defended back to the bowler.
Angled around off, Jayed pushes at it but is beaten.
Fuller and on off, defended back by Mehidy.

FOUR LEG BYES! Handy runs. Flighted and outside leg, Mehidy tries to reverse sweep but misses. It takes his pads and races behind to fine leg for a boundary. Given as runs, maybe there was some inside edge involved.
Loopy and on off, Hasan leans forward and defends it to the off side
Spinning down the leg side, Mehidy allows it through.
Helps it off his pads to mid-wicket, not in the gap.
Once again Mehidy flicks it on the leg side but not in the gap. Abu will be on strike now!
Full on off, pushed to short cover.
On off, pushed to the off side off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, Jayed pushes the ball to the off side without any fuss.
Outside off, Jayed goes for poking at it but is beaten.
On off, kept out.
On middle and leg, turned out to short leg.
SIX! Floated around off, Mehidy comes down the track and lofts it high and long over long off for a biggie.
On off, Hasan comes on the front foot to defend it.
FOUR! Hasan keeping Bangladesh's hopes alive. Full and around middle, Mehidy slog sweeps it through square leg and fetches a boundary. 29 needed more.
Tossed up on middle, played to mid-wicket.
Full and down leg, Hasan goes for the sweep but misses it completely. 10 from the over!
On off, pushed to silly point.
Another tossed up delivery on off, it's pushed to silly point again.
Beaten! Men crowding around the batsmen. Tossed up on around off, Jayed looks to defend it but the ball spins away past his outside edge.
On off, pushed away to the off side.
Another tossed up ball on off, Jayed is solid in defense.
On middle, Jayed keeps it out safely.
Flatter through the air, full and on middle, Mehidy goes on the back foot and blocks.
Flighted and on middle, Mehidy with confused footwork tries to defend but it takes the inside edge and rolls behind to square leg.
Floated and on middle, defended across the line, wide of short leg.
SIX! This one has been dispatched! 23 more needed. Loopy delivery around middle, Mehidy shimmies down the track and dispatches it over mid-wicket. This is getting close.
FOUR! Mehidy is doing it for Bangladesh, 19 more to win. He brings out the reverse sweep and shows guts of steel. Fetches it from around middle and nails it behind point.
Cornwall bowls it slower through the air and around leg, Mehidy clips it in front of square leg for one. Retains strike. 21 off Rahkeem's last two overs.
Tossed up ball landing on middle, Mehidy stays inside the crease as he defends.
Flighted and this time the length is full around middle, Hasan is forward in defense.

OUT! CAUGHT AT FIRST SLIP! SERIES WIN FOR WEST INDIES! Ecstacy in their camp, agony on the faces of the players of Bangladesh! The West Indian players are jumping in joy, what a win for them! Outstanding catch, it is. A flatter delivery, close to off and turning away, Mehidy gets back to push inside the line but it takes the outside edge and dies in front of Cornwall. The big man is quick to go down low as he snaps it inches above the surface. A massive series win achieved by West Indies as they thump Bangladesh by 17 runs!
